title: For Sale:  PRICE REDUCED - AK47
postcontent: For sale is an oldie but a goodie...my Romanian AKM style WASR 10/63 AK47. Rifle has been modified to accept double stack surplus mags with no mag wobble. Has chrome lined barrel and Tapco G2 trigger group and professionally polished rails and internals, eliminating rough action and allowing for smooth and flawless functioning without bolt sticking like some other Romanian AK's I have handled. Included is one Flambeau rifle case, sling, one ten round Tapco magazine, two 30 round magazine rebuild kits, and approximately 50 rounds of 7.62x39 ammunition (mixed). Many hours of work went into making this gun function the way you want your rifle to function - without hanging up and sticking when you pull back the charging handle to chamber a round. California compliant magazine lock (aka bullet button) installed to make rifle CA legal, easily removed with Allen wrench if you live in a state that does not require one. Approximately 400 rounds fired total without any problems. Rifle was put in the safe and has stayed there for a few years following some training courses I went through with the rifle. Has some minor cosmetic wear on the finish and furniture from the training course action it saw, but nothing that a little TLC won't fix and have looking brand new again in one sitting. I had planned to do so myself, but I finally decided to part with several of my guns right now to cover unexpected medical expenses that recently came up. Willing to ship to FFL on buyers dime but prefer a face to face transaction at Gussler's in Santee. With the recent executive orders issued by President Obama, these are no longer being imported into the United States, so if you ever want to own one, get it while you still can. I have heard from several friends in different areas of law enforcement that Kalashnikov platforms (among other non-domestic "assault rifles") will not be transferable in 2014 when new legislature has been passed and/or executive orders have been implemented. Please no insulting low ball offers, I am not in a hurry to sell and they will be ignored. I feel this is appropriately priced for the entire package, especially considering the current political climate.
